{"body":"Parent: #23\n\n## Goal\nDocument the smallest reliable two-way sync model for TyLog/TypstSeq before changing runtime behavior.\n\n## Context\nIssue #23 asks for near-realtime collaboration on Android. Current app already has a file-first vault and WebDAV/Nextcloud sync code, but near-realtime collaboration must avoid silent overwrites and Android background assumptions.\n\n## Scope\n- Define source-of-truth rules for local `.typ` files vs remote WebDAV files.\n- Define metadata used to detect remote changes: ETag/Last-Modified/content hash as available.\n- Define sync states: idle, dirty local, remote newer, syncing, conflict, offline/error.\n- Define platform limits for Android: foreground/resume/manual sync first; background sync only as later enhancement if needed.\n- Decide polling/debounce intervals for “near realtime” in an open app.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- A short design note is added to `PLAN.md` or docs and linked from #23.\n- It explicitly says when TyLog uploads, downloads, skips, or raises conflict.\n- It keeps plain files as the source of truth and does not introduce a database.\n- It names the follow-up implementation issues and dependencies.\n","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a5jg","name":"type:decision","description":"Architecture/product decision record","color":"5319e7"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a6VA","name":"status:planned","description":"Planned future work","color":"fbca04"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a7AA","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"b60205"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3bA1A","name":"area:sync","description":"Nextcloud/WebDAV/file sync","color":"17becf"}],"number":24,"state":"OPEN","title":"Sync: define reliable two-way sync model for WebDAV/Android","url":"https://github.com/berlogabob/TypstSeq/issues/24"}
--- ISSUE #25 ---
{"body":"Parent: #23\n\nDepends on: sync model/design issue from #23.\n\n## Goal\nMake two-way WebDAV sync usable while the Android app is open: local edits upload, remote edits are discovered, and the user can force a sync.\n\n## Scope\n- Add an explicit `Sync Now` action for deterministic testing and recovery.\n- On app start/resume, pull remote changes before editing when possible.\n- After local save, debounce and push changed files.\n- While app is open, poll WebDAV at a conservative interval for remote changes.\n- Rebuild the vault/index after downloaded remote changes.\n- Show sync status/error in the UI without blocking local editing.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- Editing a local note and pressing/triggering sync uploads the changed `.typ` file to WebDAV.\n- Editing the same remote file from another client and syncing in TyLog downloads it into the vault.\n- App resume triggers a best-effort remote refresh.\n- Failed network sync leaves local files intact and exposes a retry path.\n- Covered by unit/widget tests around sync state transitions where practical.\n","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a36g","name":"type:feature","description":"New user-visible capability","color":"0e8a16"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a6VA","name":"status:planned","description":"Planned future work","color":"fbca04"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a7AA","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"b60205"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3bA1A","name":"area:sync","description":"Nextcloud/WebDAV/file sync","color":"17becf"}],"number":25,"state":"OPEN","title":"Sync: implement incremental pull/push loop with manual Sync Now","url":"https://github.com/berlogabob/TypstSeq/issues/25"}
