{"body":"Parent: #23\nRelated: #13\n\n## Goal\nPrevent near-realtime two-way sync from silently overwriting local or remote edits.\n\n## Scope\n- Track enough metadata to know whether local and remote both changed since last successful sync.\n- If both changed, stop automatic overwrite and mark the note as conflicted.\n- Preserve both versions as plain files/content.\n- Surface conflict state in the UI with a simple manual resolution path.\n- Detect existing Nextcloud conflict-copy filenames and show them rather than hiding them.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- A remote-newer file is not overwritten by a stale local upload.\n- A local dirty file is not overwritten by a remote pull without an explicit conflict state.\n- Conflict files are visible to the user and never auto-deleted.\n- Tests cover remote-newer, local-newer, and both-changed cases.\n","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a4Og","name":"type:hardening","description":"Reliability, platform, release, or edge-case hardening","color":"d93f0b"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a6VA","name":"status:planned","description":"Planned future work","color":"fbca04"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a7AA","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"b60205"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3bA1A","name":"area:sync","description":"Nextcloud/WebDAV/file sync","color":"17becf"}],"number":26,"state":"OPEN","title":"Sync: add overwrite guards and conflict surfacing for two-way sync","url":"https://github.com/berlogabob/TypstSeq/issues/26"}
