{"body":"Parent: #23\n\n## Goal\nMake the limits of “almost realtime collaboration” clear in the Android UI and provide safe controls.\n\n## Scope\n- Show last sync time and current sync state.\n- Show non-blocking banners for offline/error/conflict/remote-updated states.\n- Add a lightweight “remote changes available / reload” flow if the active note changes remotely.\n- Keep automatic behavior conservative: no aggressive background polling unless proven necessary.\n- Document that this is near-realtime file sync, not Google-Docs-style live CRDT editing.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- User can see whether sync is current, running, failed, or conflicted.\n- Remote updates to the currently open note do not silently replace unsaved local edits.\n- User has an obvious manual refresh/retry action.\n- Android background limitations are documented in the issue/design note.\n","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a36g","name":"type:feature","description":"New user-visible capability","color":"0e8a16"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a6VA","name":"status:planned","description":"Planned future work","color":"fbca04"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3a7bg","name":"priority:normal","description":"Normal priority","color":"d4c5f9"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3bA1A","name":"area:sync","description":"Nextcloud/WebDAV/file sync","color":"17becf"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTLZwtc8AAAACp3bBPg","name":"area:ui","description":"UI/UX/layout","color":"9467bd"}],"number":27,"state":"OPEN","title":"Sync: near-realtime collaboration UX and Android constraints","url":"https://github.com/berlogabob/TypstSeq/issues/27"}
