# Issue #23 Android near-realtime sync plan

## Problem
Android near-realtime two-way sync is unreliable. Users report stale remote edits, delayed pulls, and overwrite/conflict confusion.

## Root-cause snapshot from current code
1. Sync is mostly startup/manual/save-triggered; no continuous remote pull loop while app is open.
2. Lifecycle transitions (resume/pause) are not explicit sync checkpoints.
3. Decision logic relies on remote `getlastmodified` vs local mtime, prone to skew/granularity issues.
4. No persisted ETag/hash cursor and no robust conflict-safe decision history.
5. Android background constraints are not explicitly modeled in the sync policy.

